This paper deals with content dissemination in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of ad hoc communication and opportunistic networks, which are relevant to the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper proposes a framework for minimizing the load on the wireless infrastructure, which is related to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also uses a large-scale dataset to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed framework, which is relevant to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
